is here from HIRA!

780
00:56:58,790 --> 00:57:01,167
He had requested an exemption!

781
00:57:01,251 --> 00:57:04,045
But like I told you,
Dr. Lee Jong-hyeok retired.

782
00:57:04,629 --> 00:57:07,006
We had only two orthopedics specialists,

783
00:57:07,090 --> 00:57:09,425
but now we're left with one.
Do you think he had a choice?

784
00:57:10,051 --> 00:57:11,928
-Is that true?
-Of course, it is!

785
00:57:12,011 --> 00:57:15,181
And stop asking me about who reported you.

786
00:57:15,265 --> 00:57:17,767
You're the one
who's being investigated right now!

787
00:57:17,851 --> 00:57:20,437
I've already done more than
I should for you. I'm hanging up!

788
00:57:24,732 --> 00:57:25,984
Damn it.

789
00:58:12,906 --> 00:58:13,907
Why you?

790
00:58:15,700 --> 00:58:16,951
Why did you come?

791
00:58:18,495 --> 00:58:19,704
Why didn't you tell me?

792
00:58:21,414 --> 00:58:22,373
Because if I did,

793
00:58:23,041 --> 00:58:24,626
you would've stopped what you were doing.

794
00:58:24,709 --> 00:58:26,127
HOSPITAL DIRECTOR CANDIDATES

795
00:58:26,211 --> 00:58:28,463
If I'd told you I'd be investigating,

796
00:58:28,546 --> 00:58:30,256
there was a chance you'd change your plan.

797
00:58:30,340 --> 00:58:32,008
CANDIDATES
CHIEF OF ORTHOPEDICS KIM TAE-SANG

798
00:58:34,010 --> 00:58:35,261
Hey.

799
00:58:35,345 --> 00:58:37,430
Find all cases of patients
in the US and Japan,

800
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:39,807
who had replacement arthroplasty
in their 40s.

801
00:58:39,891 --> 00:58:40,892
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

802
00:58:41,392 --> 00:58:43,645
Also, find patients to interview.

803
00:58:43,728 --> 00:58:46,898
People whom I operated on recently
that were successful.

804
00:58:46,981 --> 00:58:48,191
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

805
00:58:55,240 --> 00:58:56,616
Did you know then?

806
00:59:01,454 --> 00:59:03,039
That you'd be sent?

807
00:59:18,304 --> 00:59:19,889
What did you report?

808
00:59:21,641 --> 00:59:22,892
That the deputy director

809
00:59:23,851 --> 00:59:26,813
-performed unnecessary joint replacements.
-You submitted a civil complaint?

810
00:59:28,690 --> 00:59:30,400
It won't put you in a tough spot.

811
00:59:31,109 --> 00:59:33,903
They know you're my brother,
so they won't send you.

812
00:59:35,488 --> 00:59:36,573
Just play dumb.

813
00:59:36,656 --> 00:59:37,949
What about you?

814
00:59:39,325 --> 00:59:40,952
What if it puts you in a tough spot?

815
00:59:44,664 --> 00:59:45,623
Then, that's too bad.

816
00:59:46,291 --> 00:59:47,500
Why was that necessary?

817
00:59:49,627 --> 00:59:53,214
He claims to have done 5,600 surgeries,
but that's not a realistic number.

818
00:59:56,801 --> 00:59:58,094
The deputy director…

819
00:59:59,679 --> 01:00:01,556
You said he's not fit to be a director.

820
01:00:04,726 --> 01:00:06,144
It's not just for you.

821
01:00:06,978 --> 01:00:08,146
If that's what you thought,

822
01:00:08,229 --> 01:00:10,857
I'm sure Uncle Bo-hun
would've thought the same.

823
01:00:11,941 --> 01:00:13,067
He would be sad

824
01:00:14,277 --> 01:00:15,570
if just anyone succeeded him.

825
01:00:25,997 --> 01:00:27,707
He performed 5,600 surgeries in a year.

826
01:00:29,500 --> 01:00:31,669
A surgery that is only performed
as a last resort

827
01:00:31,753 --> 01:00:33,421
on patients with end-stage arthritis.

828
01:00:34,672 --> 01:00:36,174
But 5,600 people?

829
01:01:34,148 --> 01:01:35,358
That must be a habit.

830
01:01:36,275 --> 01:01:37,610
Doing this when you're focused.

831
01:01:39,404 --> 01:01:40,238
I don't do that.

832
01:01:40,321 --> 01:01:41,572
Yes, you do.

833
01:01:41,656 --> 01:01:43,574
Hasn't it been decided already?

834
01:01:43,658 --> 01:01:45,910
The question is, who will it be?

835
01:01:45,993 --> 01:01:47,286
Deputy Director Kim.

836
01:01:47,370 --> 01:01:49,622
We were the ones
who had to bear the burden!

837
01:01:50,289 --> 01:01:53,084
While one punk
pretended to be some noble guy

838
01:01:53,167 --> 01:01:55,545
with determination
and the rest acted like philanthropists,

839
01:01:55,628 --> 01:01:58,339
we had to work our asses off
to pick up the slack!

840
01:01:59,507 --> 01:02:01,134
If the deputy director
loses his candidacy,

841
01:02:01,217 --> 01:02:04,137
who will jump into the race for director?

842
01:02:04,220 --> 01:02:05,638
He pulled them out of the game.

843
01:02:05,722 --> 01:02:07,640
The fourth and fifth batters specifically.

844
01:02:07,724 --> 01:02:09,767
The chief of the Cancer Center
and the deputy director

845
01:02:09,851 --> 01:02:11,519
were the lead candidates.

846
01:02:11,602 --> 01:02:14,188
Why must it be one of those two?

847
01:02:14,272 --> 01:02:17,608
You're the first female chief
of the Neurosurgery Center.

848
01:02:17,692 --> 01:02:20,153
Why must that be the highest position
you hold?

849
01:02:24,574 --> 01:02:29,579
